Re-examined by THE ATTORNEY-GENERAL. This is Mrs. King's photo
graph (produced); the face is very much like her—it was the loud talk
ing which attracted my attention, and I went part of the way downstairs—after being before the Magistrate I talked to my husband and different people about the case and about the woman being found—it was the talk of the neighbourhood—I don't know the date when I went to the Treasury—the earrings I admired had a fringe, and so had those which were shown me—they looked so nice that they attracted my attention—I know Miss Wilmore—I remember her coming to 84 and 215.;
